we had a similar structure with thrift and found that it's limiting and makes operations/upgrades harder.
let's go with something very simple and generic
message request {
  map<string,string> request_header;
  string sql; //optional
  repeated string segments;
  repeated byte payload; 
}

Let's make response generic and include the metadata:
map<string, string> metadata = 1;
bytes payload = 2;

